{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868997810,"sessionID":"ses_285f5acf8ffek1l1CTQ0sUQCKO","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0a6cf0001tb08CHRERPyBoq","messageID":"msg_d7a0a6440001D7vLo91pFO6IiH","sessionID":"ses_285f5acf8ffek1l1CTQ0sUQCKO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d9f7445715434ab892dac984","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** sdk-python  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete - Implementation Pending)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: Project Structure & Utilities (T001-T004)\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Create `pyproject.toml` for `agentcube-sdk` package with dependencies: `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`\n15:   - *File:* `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n16:   - *Verify:* Package builds with `python -m build`, requires Python >=3.10\n17: \n18: - [ ] **T002** Create `agentcube/exceptions.py` with exception hierarchy\n19:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n20:   - *Verify:* `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError` all defined; `CommandExecutionError` is subclass of `AgentCubeError`\n21:   - *Test:* Import and instantiate each exception\n22: \n23: - [ ] **T003** Create utility modules: `agentcube/utils/http.py`, `agentcube/utils/utils.py`, `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n24:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py` - `create_session()` with HTTPAdapter\n25:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py` - `read_token_from_file(file_path) -> str`\n26:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py` - `get_logger(name, level) -> logging.Logger`\n27:   - *Verify:* All functions importable and work as specified in design.md\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T004** Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` module marker\n30:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n31:   - *Verify:* Empty file, creates valid Python package\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Phase 2: Control Plane Client (T005-T008)\n36: \n37: - [ ] **T005** Implement `ControlPlaneClient` class with constructor\n38:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n39:   - *Verify:* Accepts `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n40:   - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify default values\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T006** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata, ttl)` \n43:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n44:   - *Verify:* POSTs to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body, returns `sessionId` from response\n45:   - *Test:* Call create_session, verify correct HTTP request and response parsing\n46: \n47: - [ ] **T007** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session(session_id)`\n48:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n49:   - *Verify:* DELETE to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`, returns `True` on 404, logs and returns `False` on other failures\n50:   - *Test:* Test 404 response returns True\n51: \n52: - [ ] **T008** Implement `ControlPlaneClient.close()`\n53:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n54:   - *Verify:* Closes HTTP session\n55:   - *Test:* Verify session is closed after close() call\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Phase 3: Code Interpreter Data Plane Client (T009-T017)\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T009** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` class with constructor\n62:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n63:   - *Verify:* Accepts `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`, `base_url`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n64:   - *Test:* Instantiate with router_url+namespace+cr_name, verify base_url constructed correctly\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T010** Implement base URL construction from router components\n67:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n68:   - *Verify:* When `base_url` not provided, constructs `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n69:   - *Test:* Verify correct URL format\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T011** Implement `_request()` helper with session header\n72:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n73:   - *Verify:* Adds `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` header to all requests\n74:   - *Test:* Make request, verify header present\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T012** Implement `execute_command(command, timeout)` via data plane\n77:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n78:   - *Verify:* POSTs to `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`, read_timeout = timeout + 2.0\n79:   - *Test:* Execute command, verify request format\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T013** Implement `write_file(content, remote_path)` via data plane\n82:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n83:   - *Verify:* POSTs to `api/files` with base64 encoded content, path, mode \"0644\"\n84:   - *Test:* Write file, verify request body format\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T014** Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` via data plane\n87:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n88:   - *Verify:* POST multipart form data to `api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n89:   - *Test:* Upload file, verify multipart request\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T015** Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` via data plane\n92:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n93:   - *Verify:* GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`, writes to local path\n94:   - *Test:* Download file, verify stream handling\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T016** Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` via data plane\n97:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n98:   - *Verify:* GET `api/files` with query parameter `path`\n99:   - *Test:* List files, verify query param\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T017** Implement `close()` method\n102:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n103:   - *Verify:* Closes HTTP session\n104:   - *Test:* Verify session closed\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Phase 4: Code Interpreter Client (T018-T026)\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T018** Implement `CodeInterpreterClient` class with constructor\n111:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n112:   - *Verify:* Accepts `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose=False`, `session_id=None`\n113:   - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify defaults\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T019** Implement router URL validation\n116:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n117:   - *Verify:* Raises `ValueError` if neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` env var is set\n118:   - *Test:* Instantiate without router_url, verify ValueError raised\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T020** Implement `_init_data_plane()` and session creation\n121:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n122:   - *Verify:* If no `session_id` provided, calls `cp_client.create_session()`, then initializes data plane client\n123:   - *Test:* Instantiate without session_id, verify create_session called\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T021** Implement data plane init failure handling\n126:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n127:   - *Verify:* If `_init_data_plane()` fails after session created, logs warning, deletes session, sets session_id to None, re-raises\n128:   - *Test:* Simulate failure, verify cleanup\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T022** Implement context manager protocol (`__enter__`, `__exit__`)\n131:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n132:   - *Verify:* `__exit__` calls `stop()`, which closes data plane and deletes control plane session if it was created by this client\n133:   - *Test:* Use client as context manager, verify cleanup on exit\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T023** Implement `execute_command(command, timeout)`\n136:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n137:   - *Verify:* Delegates to data plane client, raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit code\n138:   - *Test:* Execute command with exit code != 0, verify exception\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T024** Implement `run_code(language, code, timeout)`\n141:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n142:   - *Verify:* For python/py/python3, writes timestamped `.py` file, executes with `python3`\n143:   - *Test:* Run python code, verify execution\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T025** Implement file operations (`write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`)\n146:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n147:   - *Verify:* Delegate to data plane client methods\n148:   - *Test:* Each operation works correctly\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T026** Implement `stop()` method\n151:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n152:   - *Verify:* Closes data plane session, deletes control plane session if created by this client\n153:   - *Test:* Call stop, verify cleanup\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ### Phase 5: Package Exports (T027-T028)\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T027** Create `agentcube/__init__.py` with public exports\n160:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n161:   - *Verify:* `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`, imports both classes\n162:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient`\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T028** Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with client exports\n165:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n166:   - *Verify:* `__all__ = [\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n167:   - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient`\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ### Phase 6: AgentRuntimeClient Stub (T029-T031)\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T029** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class stub\n174:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n175:   - *Verify:* Basic class structure per design.md (full implementation in AR-028)\n176:   - *Test:* Instantiate client\n177: \n178: - [ ] **T030** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class stub\n179:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n180:   - *Verify:* Basic structure per design.md (full implementation in AR-028)\n181:   - *Test:* Instantiate client\n182: \n183: - [ ] **T031** Add AgentRuntimeClient to package exports\n184:   - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n185:   - *Verify:* Already exported in T027\n186:   - *Test:* Import and use\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ### Phase 7: Integration & Tests (T032-T036)\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T032** Write unit tests for exception hierarchy\n193:   - *File:* `sdk-python/tests/test_exceptions.py`\n194:   - *Verify:* Each exception can be instantiated and has correct attributes\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T033** Write unit tests for ControlPlaneClient\n197:   - *File:* `sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py`\n198:   - *Verify:* create_session, delete_session work correctly\n199: \n200: - [ ] **T034** Write unit tests for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n201:   - *File:* `sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n202:   - *Verify:* All operations make correct HTTP requests\n203: \n204: - [ ] **T035** Write unit tests for CodeInterpreterClient\n205:   - *File:* `sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py`\n206:   - *Verify:* Full lifecycle, context manager, error handling\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T036** Create example usage scripts\n209:   - *File:* `sdk-python/examples/basic_usage.py`\n210:   - *Verify:* Demonstrates CodeInterpreterClient usage\n211: \n212: ---\n213: \n214: ## Dependencies\n215: \n216: | Task | Depends On |\n217: |------|------------|\n218: | T002 | T001 |\n219: | T003 | T001 |\n220: | T004 | T001 |\n221: | T005 | T001, T002, T003 |\n222: | T006 | T005 |\n223: | T007 | T005 |\n224: | T008 | T005 |\n225: | T009 | T001, T003 |\n226: | T010 | T009 |\n227: | T011 | T009 |\n228: | T012 | T010, T011 |\n229: | T013 | T010, T011 |\n230: | T014 | T010, T011 |\n231: | T015 | T010, T011 |\n232: | T016 | T010, T011 |\n233: | T017 | T009 |\n234: | T018 | T001, T002, T003, T005 |\n235: | T019 | T018 |\n236: | T020 | T005, T009 |\n237: | T021 | T020 |\n238: | T022 | T020, T026 |\n239: | T023 | T020 |\n240: | T024 | T020, T023 |\n241: | T025 | T020 |\n242: | T026 | T017, T007 |\n243: | T027 | T018, T029 |\n244: | T028 | T005, T009, T030 |\n245: | T029 | T001, T003 |\n246: | T030 | T001, T003 |\n247: | T031 | T029 |\n248: | T032 | T002 |\n249: | T033 | T005, T006, T007 |\n250: | T034 | T009-T017 |\n251: | T035 | T018-T026 |\n252: | T036 | T018 |\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## Verification Checklist\n257: \n258: - [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient constructs with proper defaults (name, namespace, ttl, verbose)\n259: - [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient creates session via ControlPlaneClient when session_id not provided\n260: - [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n261: - [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient handles data plane init failure with session cleanup\n262: - [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n263: - [ ] AC006: execute_command raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit code\n264: - [ ] AC007: run_code supports python/py/python3 languages with timestamped file execution\n265: - [ ] AC008: write_file creates remote files with base64 content and mode 0644\n266: - [ ] AC009: upload_file uploads files via multipart to data plane\n267: - [ ] AC010: download_file downloads files as streams to local path\n268: - [ ] AC011: list_files returns file listing from data plane\n269: - [ ] AC012: stop closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n270: - [ ] AC013: ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns sessionId from response\n271: - [ ] AC014: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session returns True on 404\n272: - [ ] AC015: ControlPlaneClient resolves base_url and auth from env/args\n273: - [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n274: - [ ] AC017: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all data plane requests\n275: - [ ] AC018: Exception hierarchy includes AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError\n276: - [ ] AC019: Default timeouts are 120s read, 5.0s connect\n277: - [ ] AC020: Connection pool defaults are 10 connections, 10 max size\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## References\n282: \n283: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md`\n284: - Base Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n285: - Code Execution Design: `code-execution/design.md` (PicoD API)\n\n(End of file - total 285 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete - Implementation Pending)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Project Structure & Utilities (T001-T004)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `pyproject.toml` for `agentcube-sdk` package with dependencies: `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`\n  - *File:* `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n  - *Verify:* Package builds with `python -m build`, requires Python >=3.10\n\n- [ ] **T002** Create `agentcube/exceptions.py` with exception hierarchy\n  - *File:* `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n  - *Verify:* `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError` all defined; `CommandExecutionError` is subclass of `AgentCubeError`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775868997786,"end":1775868997807}}}}
