{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869002485,"sessionID":"ses_285f5acf8ffek1l1CTQ0sUQCKO","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0a7ece001o7mPK6nZYSlm7x","messageID":"msg_d7a0a70e4001BGXd1KZ8fl0R2j","sessionID":"ses_285f5acf8ffek1l1CTQ0sUQCKO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_87834bf11af844fa9db914a5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-027\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n20: 1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n21: 2. Execute commands, run code, and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n22: 3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Requirements\n27: \n28: ### AR-027-001: CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n29: \n30: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n33: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n34: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n35: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n38: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n39: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n40: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-C — Router URL required\n43: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n44: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n48: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n49: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 284. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-027\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869002467,"end":1775869002482}}}}
