{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869077507,"sessionID":"ses_285f5acf8ffek1l1CTQ0sUQCKO","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0b2cb10011EDBnBPBoklreH","messageID":"msg_d7a0b2247001kuY1sD0DA8TCJo","sessionID":"ses_285f5acf8ffek1l1CTQ0sUQCKO","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_8816ff2dc7884c1c882734f5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Agent Runtime sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute tools/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n2. Execute tools and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n3. Query available tools and their schemas\n4. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-002: Tool Execution\n\nThe system SHALL provide a method to execute tools via the data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Execute tool with parameters\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"calculator\", parameters={\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, timeout=30)` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}/api/execute` with JSON body `{\"tool_name\": \"calculator\", \"parameters\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, \"timeout\": \"30s\"}`\n- **AND** return the result from the data plane\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Execute tool timeout\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"slow-tool\", parameters={}, timeout=5)` is called\n- **AND** the tool takes longer than 5 seconds\n- **THEN** the client SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with timeout information\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-003: Tool Discovery\n\nThe system SHALL provide methods to discover available tools and their schemas.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — List available tools\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `list_tools()` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools`\n- **AND** return a list of tool names\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Get tool schema\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `get_tool_schema(tool_name=\"calculator\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools/calculator/schema`\n- **AND** return the tool's input/output schema\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-004: File Operations\n\nThe system SHALL provide file operation methods via the data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Upload file\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/data.csv\", remote_path=\"/data/input.csv\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST multipart form data to `{base_url}/api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **AND** the file SHALL be available at `/data/input.csv` in the runtime\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Download file\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/output/result.csv\", local_path=\"/tmp/result.csv\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files/output/result.csv` with `stream=True`\n- **AND** write the content to `/tmp/result.csv`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-C — List files\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/data\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files?path=/data`\n- **AND** return a list of files in that directory\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-005: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Base URL from router components\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `cr_name=\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Explicit base URL\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-006: Session Header\n\nAll data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Session header on requests\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** any data plane method is called (e.g., `execute_tool`, `list_tools`)\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n- Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n- WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n- Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n- Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n| workload-manager/api.md | Control plane API specification |\n| router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters | Unit test |\n| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient creates session when session_id not provided | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-003 | Context manager properly cleans up resources | Integration test |\n| AC-004 | Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-005 | ValueError raised when router_url missing | Unit test |\n| AC-006 | execute_tool makes correct HTTP POST | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-007 | list_tools makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-008 | get_tool_schema makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-009 | File operations use correct endpoints and headers | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-010 | stop() closes all connections and deletes session | Unit test with mock |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n- Use the existing `ControlPlaneClient` from AR-027 for session management\n- Leverage the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n- Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869077495,"end":1775869077504}}}}
